com.karacasoft.cardboardui.view

Class ImageButton3D

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.karacasoft.cardboardui.view.View3D
      • com.karacasoft.cardboardui.view.Button3D
        • com.karacasoft.cardboardui.view.ImageButton3D

  • public class ImageButton3D
extends Button3D
    A subclass of Button3D that is used to show a custom image on a normal Button3D. If you want to display an image right next to the Button. You might want to check Button3D.setDrawableLeft(int, int) and Button3D.setDrawableRight(int, int). Created by Karaca on 6/3/2015.

      • measure

        public void measure()
        Description copied from class: View3D
        A view's width, height and depth, depends on the View itself. So every specialized view subclass should implement its own measure method to calculate its width, height and depth. It is possible to leave these fields empty. But for convenience, subclasses should implement a measure method for each View.
